  , issueCommentBody =
      "Can you try adding a `.coerceTo('ARRAY')` after the value for `routines` like this:\r\n```\r\nr.db('mydb').table('workouts').get('0e4c4970-cd9d-47e4-b14f-e85c66a4db7d').merge(function (workout) {\r\n  return {\r\n    routines: r.db('mydb').table('routines').filter(function (routine) {\r\n      return workout('routines').contains(routine('id'));\r\n    }).coerceTo('ARRAY')\r\n  }\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nI think the problem is that `r.table(...).filter(...)` returns a stream, which cannot directly be stored into the field of an object unless it's first converted into an array.\r\n\r\nI think this is probably going to be addressed by https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/2721 eventually."
  , issueCommentId = 74178573
